    "abstract": "Cuban American José Bedia's artistic practice mirrors ethnography through his close examination of cultural performance and ritual, material culture, imagery, and storytelling. He is a participant-observer of cultural ways of knowing, which become synthesized in his art. His fieldwork with the Semana Santa in Mexico, the Lakota in North America, and Afro-Transatlantic cultures such as Le Regla Kongo, Regla de Ocho, and the Leopard Society of Abakuas, to name a few, is reflected in his artistic practice. He immerses himself into the place and with the event as a learner, making sketches, taking photographs, and writing notes. These understandings appear in his art.",
